section.para:
The distributed tarball, should already contain this file, which during the installation (i.e. make install step at
        ) process is copyied (with the right privileges, at ${EPREFIX}/share 
        see ).

answer.para:
In function iers2010::gpt2, found in the source file src/gpt2.cpp there is a DEFINE statement (at the top of the source file), similar to:
/** @brief Define the path to the gpt2_5.grd file (including the filename) */ #define PATH_TO_GRD25_GRD "/usr/local/share/gpt2_5.grd"
This line is set during the installation procedure, and the path is automatically set to reflect the datarootdir directory.

You can also choose to ommit this last part (i.e. modifying the source code) and provide the path to the grid file at
                        evey call to iers2010::gpt2. That means writting:

void foo ( parameter_list )
{
    int status;
    // do various things ...
    status = iers2010::gpt2 ();
    // do more things ...
}

                        instead of

void foo ( parameter_list )
{
    int status;
    // do various things ...
    status = iers2010::gpt2 ();
    // do more things ...
}
